           ] )
         ]
       ] ) ;
       fhir:linkId [ fhir:v "EmCare.B11S1.DE01-help" ] ;
       fhir:text [ fhir:v "A young infant has diarrhoea if the stools have changed from the usual pattern, and are many and watery. This means more water than faecal matter. The normally frequent or semi-solid stools of a breastfed baby are not diarrhoea.<br />\nThe mother of a breastfed young infant can recognize diarrhoea because the consistency or frequency of the stools is different than normal." ] ;
       fhir:type [ fhir:v "display" ]
     ] )
